# Vibes Project Structure & Conventions

## Project Overview
The Vibes project is a Next.js 14 application using the App Router, TypeScript, and focused on showcasing "good vibes" with a clean, simple interface.

## Directory Structure
```
vibes/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx          # Root layout with Navigation
│   ├── page.tsx            # Home page
│   ├── globals.css         # Global styles
│   ├── components/         # Shared components
│   │   └── Navigation.tsx  # Main navigation component
│   └── about/              # About page route
├── .cursor/rules/          # Cursor AI rules
└── package.json            # Dependencies and scripts
```

## Key Project Files
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Main layout with navigation and padding
- [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Homepage content
- [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Global styling
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project configuration

## Development Standards
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: CSS (no framework dependencies currently)
- **Components**: Functional components with proper TypeScript interfaces

## Metadata Standards
All pages should include proper metadata for SEO:
```tsx
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title - Vibes',
  description: 'Descriptive text about the page content',
}
```

## Navigation Structure
- Main navigation is handled by the Navigation component
- Layout includes 80px top padding to account for fixed navigation
- Keep navigation consistent across all pages

## Styling Approach
- Global styles in `app/globals.css`
- Inline styles used sparingly for layout adjustments
- Focus on clean, minimal design that reflects "good vibes"

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run start` - Start production server
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint
- `npm run export` - Build and export static site
